  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed&amp;nbsp;alterations to the roof to form an end gable and rear dormer&amp;nbsp;with their unsympathetic&amp;nbsp;design and unduly bulky scale, and&amp;nbsp;the replacement of the&amp;nbsp;existing timber windows with lack of sufficient justification and inappropriate window material and type,&amp;nbsp;would be harmful to the character and appearance of the host dwelling and the Pinnerwood Park Estate Conservation Area and would also fail to preserve or enhance the setting of that conservation area. The development would therefore be contrary to the high-quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023), policies D3 (D(1) and D(11)) and HC1 of The London Plan (2021), policy CS1.B of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), policies DM1 and DM7 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013), the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010) and the Pinnerwood Park Conservation Area Management Strategy (2009).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
